<hr>
<i>Posted by Necosi on 11-05-2002 11:49 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>Trillian isn't an IM program.  It's an application (3rd party) that links all the messengers together.  You still have to have Yahoo Messenger, or AOL, or MSN, etc, but you can chat to any through it.<br />
<br />
I.E.  My buddy can only use MSN at work.  I use Yahoo from home because it's the only I really liked.  So, using my Yahoo account, I activate Trillian, and I can chat to him through his MSN account.<!-- BEGIN TEMPLATE: postbit_signature -->
